OL,3,CCouncil to spend #440,000 guarding
OL,4,Cempty road
OL,6,FThe council has decided to pay for
OL,7,Fwork to get the road into use before
OL,8,Fseeking compensation from the
OL,9,Fadministrator.
OL,11,FThe road will serve the 8,000 houses
OL,12,Fwhich are eventually planned for the
OL,13,FNew Eastern Villages (NEV) expansion
OL,14,Fprogramme across the A419 from
OL,15,FCovingham and Dorcan.
OL,17,FIt runs from South Marston to just
OL,18,Fnorth of the Commonhead roundabout.
OL,20,FThe road is now owned by the
OL,21,Fadministrator Grant Thornton.
