OL,3,CCouncil to spend #440,000 guarding
OL,4,Cempty road
OL,6,FThe company wants Swindon Borough
OL,7,FCouncil to pay for the road so it can
OL,8,Fbe handed over, but the council says
OL,9,Fit is not fit for purpose and has
OL,10,Fseveral faults including a "loose road
OL,11,Fsurface" and a "crack" in the bridge.
OL,13,FThe council has announced it will pay
OL,14,Ffor the repairs to the road itself and
OL,15,Fwill seek to recover the money from
OL,16,Fthe administrator later.
OL,18,FCouncillor Chris Watts, cabinet member
OL,19,Ffor transport and the environment,
OL,20,Fsaid: "We can't risk this going on for
OL,21,Fyears and years.
